1
00:02:08,261 --> 00:02:10,695
Life is like a film

2
00:02:11,531 --> 00:02:13,897
Each of us is the lead in our own film

3
00:02:15,568 --> 00:02:19,231
Some might assume he is also
the co-lead in someone else's film

4
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,731
But in fact, his role is merely supporting

5
00:02:22,909 --> 00:02:24,501
Or just a bit part

6
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:29,280
Or worse...
his scenes could have been edited out

7
00:02:29,883 --> 00:02:31,748
He just doesn't know it

8
00:02:38,224 --> 00:02:40,351
Like the mother and child here

9
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,729
The girl will certainly be the lead
in her mother's film

10
00:02:44,564 --> 00:02:46,464
Yet, in ten years

11
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:51,002
How important would the role of the mother
be in her daughter's film?

12
00:02:55,808 --> 00:02:58,971
I'm responsible for keeping track
of these deleted footages

13
00:02:59,512 --> 00:03:01,446
I make sure they are intact

14
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:04,680
Because people do make mistakes
in editing all the time

15
00:03:05,818 --> 00:03:07,911
When they realize they made the wrong cut...

16
00:03:08,488 --> 00:03:11,048
I'd deliver the footages back to them

17
00:03:42,188 --> 00:03:46,318
The destination of my next delivery is here

18
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:06,378
The time is now

19
00:04:12,485 --> 00:04:15,045
The set is done

20
00:04:19,425 --> 00:04:22,485
The studio is lit

21
00:04:23,196 --> 00:04:25,426
The door is open

22
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:30,294
Costumes' been chosen

23
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:32,996
Vocals' been sweetened

24
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:35,104
Rhythm' been enlivened

25
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:37,607
All ready and waiting

26
00:04:37,744 --> 00:04:39,371
Shoot-the past and present

27
00:04:39,545 --> 00:04:41,570
Shoot-love and pain

28
00:04:41,681 --> 00:04:43,546
Shoot-tangled rivalries

29
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:46,048
All are nothing, but an illusion

30
00:04:46,219 --> 00:04:48,050
No less than a blink

31
00:04:48,221 --> 00:04:51,190
No more than an eternity

32
00:04:51,357 --> 00:04:55,157
It's heaven nevertheless

33
00:04:55,528 --> 00:04:58,929
How close is the present
how distant are the memories?

34
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:02,261
How stressful is the past
how tiring is the present?

35
00:05:02,402 --> 00:05:08,136
"In a world where love's forgotten
can a memory be born to last?"

36
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:11,937
What kind of a love story can pay
for your living?

37
00:05:12,078 --> 00:05:15,809
Who would allow this story the highest glory?

38
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:19,679
Perhaps all love stories do not come easy

39
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:23,812
But they're just words on a blackboard
such is the irony

40
00:05:23,956 --> 00:05:25,548
Wipe away the past and present

41
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:27,421
Wipe away love and pain

42
00:05:27,627 --> 00:05:29,288
Wipe away the rivalries

43
